Remove the chiles from the liquid, reserving the liquid, and coarsely {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/chop/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 chop}}. Place the chiles in the bowl of a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/food-processor/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 food processor}} along with 1/4 cup of the soaking liquid, honey, cilantro, garlic and pine {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/nuts/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 nuts}} and process until smooth. With the motor running, slowly add the oil until emulsified; season with salt and pepper.}